KPIs 10



TotalTickets = COUNTROWS(ZendeskTicketSystem)


Total tickets per day =

CALCULATE([TotalTickets],

    FILTER(ALL('Calendar'),

          'Calendar'[Date] > MAX('Calendar'[Date]) -1 &&

           'Calendar'[Date]<= MAX('Calendar'[Date])))

To Avoid the KPI from Displaying Blank and replace with Zero rather you can use the following syntax

Zero Avg TktsPerDay =

IF(ISBLANK(AVERAGEX(

                          VALUES('Calendar'[Date].[Date]),

                                [Total tickets per day]

)),

0,

 AVERAGEX(

                          VALUES('Calendar'[Date].[Date]),

                                [Total tickets per day]

))


Measure used for Filter

Last 12 Weeks = Var a = MAX(ZendeskTicketSystem[WksBkActual])-10

Return

IF(ZendeskTicketSystem[WksBkActual]>= a, "Last 12 Weeks", "Other Weeks")


Follow the steps to build this KPIs Avg. Tickets Per Day

1. Drag and drop card from visualization.

2. Drag and drop Avg.Tickets Per Day measure from Zendesk ticketing system table.

Formatting:

3. General

·        X-Position = 0

·        Y-Position = 89

·        Width = 199

·        Height = 94

 4. Data label

Color - #E06234

Text size - 40pt

Font family – DIN

5. Title

Title text: Avg Tickets Per Day

Font Color: White

Background Color: #03363D

Alignment: Center

Text size: 14pt

6. Category – off

7.Backround-on

Color – E6E6E6

8.  Boarder – on

Color – E6E6E6
